Aim to combine two successful items (e.g., two filtered liquids, or two extracts) of the *same feature type* (mundane+mundane or magical+magical) to reach a value of 60. Once you reach 60, it's safest to submit, as further actions often decrease value.

message: Hello! Here's what I've learned: The 'vial' tool works best on 'solid' ingredients, and the 'filter' tool works best on 'gas' or 'liquid' ingredients. Successful applications of tools yield valuable liquid items (30 points) and consume the tool. message: Hey future player! Here's what I learned: 1. Vial (ğŸ§ª) is best for Solids: Use it on any solid (mundane like Dandelion, or magical like Unicorn Horn) to get a +30 liquid extract. 2. Filter (ğŸ§«) is best for Liquids: Use it on any liquid (mundane like Honey Nectar, or magical like Kraken Ink) to get a +30 filtered liquid. 3. Avoid using the Vial on liquids or gases, and the Filter on solids or gases, as these always resulted in negative values. 4. Combining two +30 *liquid* items of the *same type* (both mundane, or both magical) will create a +60 item. This is your best path to max score. Avoid combining positive items with any negatively valued items as it typically reduces your score. Good luck!
